org.keyple.calypso.transaction

Class PoSecureSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.keyple.calypso.transaction.PoSecureSession

  • public class PoSecureSession
extends java.lang.Object
    Portable Object Secure Session. A non-encrypted secure session with a Calypso PO requires the management of two ProxyReader in order to communicate with both a Calypso PO and a CSM

                                                           java.util.List<SendableInSession> poCommandsOutsideSession)
                                                    throws org.keyple.seproxy.exceptions.IOReaderException
        Process identification. On poReader, generate a SERequest for the specified PO AID, with keepChannelOpen set at true, and apduRequests defined with the optional poCommands_OutsideSession. Returns the corresponding SEResponse. Identifies the serial and the revision of the PO from FCI data. On csmSessionReader, automatically operate the Select Diversifier and the Get Challenge.
        Parameters:
        poAid - the po AID
        poCommandsOutsideSession - the po commands outside session
        Returns:
        the SE response
        Throws:
        org.keyple.seproxy.exceptions.IOReaderException - the IO reader exception

        Process opening. On poReader, generate a SERequest with the current selected AID, with keepChannelOpen set at true, and apduRequests defined with openCommand and the optional poCommands_InsideSession. On csmSessionReader, automatically operate the Digest Init and potentially several Digest Update Multiple.

      • processClosing

        public org.keyple.seproxy.SeResponse processClosing(java.util.List<SendableInSession> poCommandsInsideSession,
                                                    java.util.List<org.keyple.seproxy.ApduResponse> poAnticipatedResponseInsideSession,
                                                    PoCommandBuilder ratificationCommand)
                                             throws org.keyple.seproxy.exceptions.IOReaderException
        Process closing. On csmSessionReader, automatically operate potentially several Digest Update Multiple, and the Digest Close. Identifies the terminal signature. On poReader, generate a SERequest with the current selected AID, with keepChannelOpen set at false, and apduRequests defined with poCommands_InsideSession, closeCommand, and ratificationCommand. Identifies the PO signature. On csmSessionReader, automatically operates the Digest Authenticate. Returns the corresponding SEResponse and the boolean status of the authentication.
        Parameters:
        poCommandsInsideSession - the po commands inside session
        poAnticipatedResponseInsideSession - The anticipated PO response in the sessions
        ratificationCommand - the ratification command
        Returns:
        SEResponse close session response
